records.name: BatchExecuteErrorDetail
records.description: Represents the properties belonging to an `sql:BatchExecuteError`.

fields.name: clause
fields.description: The actual text of the SQL definition statement

records.name: CheckConstraint
records.description: Represents a check constraint.

records.name: ColumnConfig
records.description: Defines the database column name which matches the record field. The default value is the record field name.

fields.name: 'type
fields.description: The SQL data-type associated with the column

fields.name: defaultValue
fields.description: The default value of the column

fields.name: referentialConstraints
fields.description: Referential constraints (foreign key relationships) associated with the column

records.name: ColumnDefinition
records.description: Represents a column in a table.

fields.name: maxOpenConnections
fields.description:
The maximum number of open connections that the pool is allowed to have.
Includes both idle and in-use connections. The default value is 15. This can be changed through
the configuration API with the `ballerina.sql.maxOpenConnections` key

fields.name: maxConnectionLifeTime
fields.description:
The maximum lifetime (in seconds) of a connection in the pool. The default value is 1800
seconds (30 minutes). A value of 0 indicates an unlimited maximum lifetime (infinite lifetime).
The minimum allowed value is 30 seconds. This can be changed through the configuration API
with the `ballerina.sql.maxConnectionLifeTime` key.

fields.name: minIdleConnections
fields.description:
The minimum number of idle connections that the pool tries to maintain. The default value
is the same as `maxOpenConnections` and it can be changed through the configuration
API with the `ballerina.sql.minIdleConnections` key

records.name: ConnectionPool
records.description:
Represents the properties, which are used to configure a DB connection pool.
Default values of the fields can be set through the configuration API.

records.name: DatabaseErrorDetail
records.description: Represents the properties belonging to an `sql:DatabaseError`.

fields.name: affectedRowCount
fields.description:
Number of rows affected by the execution of the query. It may be one of the following,  
(1) A number greater than or equal to zero, the count of affected rows after the successful execution of the query  
(2) A value of the `SUCCESS_NO_INFO`, the count of affected rows is unknown after the successful execution of the query  
(3) A value of the `EXECUTION_FAILED`, the query execution failed

fields.name: lastInsertId
fields.description: The ID generated by the database in response to a query execution. This can be `()` in case the database does not support this feature

records.name: ExecutionResult
records.description: Metadata of the query execution.

fields.name: mode
fields.description: The mode of the parameter (IN, OUT, INOUT)

records.name: ParameterDefinition
records.description: Represents a routine parameter.

fields.name: tableName
fields.description: The name of the table which contains the referenced column

fields.name: columnName
fields.description: The name of the referenced column

fields.name: updateRule
fields.description: The action taken when an update statement violates the constraint

fields.name: deleteRule
fields.description: The action taken when a delete statement violates the constraint

records.name: ReferentialConstraint
records.description: Represents a referential constraint (foriegn key constraint).

fields.name: 'type
fields.description: The type of the routine (procedure or function)

fields.name: returnType
fields.description: If the routine returns a value, the return data-type. Else ()

fields.name: parameters
fields.description: The parameters associated with the routine

records.name: RoutineDefinition
records.description: Represents a routine.

fields.name: 'type
fields.description: Whether the table is a base table or a view

fields.name: columns
fields.description: The columns included in the table

fields.name: checkConstraints
fields.description: Check constraints associated with the table

records.name: TableDefinition
records.description: Represents a table in the database.

methods.name: query
methods.description:
Executes the query, which may return multiple results.
When processing the stream, make sure to consume all fetched data or close the stream.

parameters.name: sqlQuery
parameters.description: The SQL query

parameters.name: returnType
parameters.description:
The `typedesc` of the record to which the result needs to be returned.
It can be a basic type if the query result contains only one column

returnParameters.description: Result in the `returnType` type or an `sql:Error`

methods.name: queryRow
methods.description:
Executes the query, which is expected to return at most one row of the result.
If the query does not return any results, `sql:NoRowsError` is returned.

parameters.name: sqlQuery
parameters.description: The SQL query

returnParameters.description: Metadata of the query execution as an `sql:ExecutionResult` or an `sql:Error`

methods.name: execute
methods.description: Executes the SQL query. Only the metadata of the execution is returned (not the results from the query).

parameters.name: sqlQueries
parameters.description: The SQL query with multiple sets of parameters

returnParameters.description: Metadata of the query execution as an `sql:ExecutionResult[]` or an `sql:Error`

methods.name: batchExecute
methods.description:
Executes the SQL query with multiple sets of parameters in a batch. Only the metadata of the execution is returned (not the results from the query).
If one of the commands in the batch fails, an `sql:BatchExecuteError` will be returned. However, the driver may
or may not continue to process the remaining commands in the batch after a failure.

parameters.name: sqlQuery
parameters.description: The SQL query

parameters.name: rowTypes
parameters.description: `typedesc` array of the records to which the results need to be returned

returnParameters.description: Summary of the execution and results are returned in an `sql:ProcedureCallResult`, or an `sql:Error`

methods.name: call
methods.description:
Executes an SQL query, which calls a stored procedure. This may or may not
return results. Once the results are processed, the `close` method on `sql:ProcedureCallResult` must be called.

returnParameters.description: Possible `sql:Error` when closing the client

methods.name: close
methods.description:
Closes the SQL client and shuts down the connection pool. The client must be closed only at the end of the
application lifetime (or closed for graceful stops in a service).

The object constructed through backtick surrounded strings. Dynamic parameters of `sql:Parameter` type can be indicated using `${<variable name>}`
such as `` `The sql:ParameterizedQuery is ${variable_name}` ``.
This validates the parameter types during the query execution.

The object constructed through backtick surrounded strings. Dynamic parameters of `sql:Value` type can be indicated using `${<variable name>}`
such as `` `The sql:ParameterizedQuery is ${variable_name}` ``.
This validates the parameter types during the query execution.

returnParameters.description: A string array containing the names of the tables or an `sql:Error`

methods.name: listTables
methods.description: Retrieves all tables in the database.

parameters.name: tableName
parameters.description: The name of the table

parameters.name: include
parameters.description:
Options on whether columnar and constraint related information should be fetched.
If `NO_COLUMNS` is provided, then no information related to columns will be retrieved.
If `COLUMNS_ONLY` is provided, then columnar information will be retrieved, but not constraint
related information.
If `COLUMNS_WITH_CONSTRAINTS` is provided, then columar information along with constraint related
information will be retrieved

returnParameters.description: An 'sql:TableDefinition' with the relevant table information or an `sql:Error`

errors.name: ApplicationError
errors.description: Represents an error originating from application-level configurations.

errors.name: BatchExecuteError
errors.description: Represents an error that occurs during the execution of batch queries.

errors.name: ConversionError
errors.description: Represents an error that occurs when a query retrieves a result that is corrupted and cannot be converted to the expected type.

errors.name: DatabaseError
errors.description:
Represents an error caused by an issue related to database accessibility, erroneous queries, constraint violations,
database resource clean-up, and other similar scenarios.

errors.name: DataError
errors.description: Represents an error that occurs during the processing of the parameters or returned results.

errors.name: Error
errors.description: Defines the generic error type for the `sql` module.

errors.name: FieldMismatchError
errors.description: Represents an error that occurs when a query retrieves a result that cannot be mapped to the expected record type.

errors.name: NoRowsError
errors.description: Represents an error that occurs when a query retrieves does not retrieve any rows when at least one row is expected.

errors.name: TypeMismatchError
errors.description: Represents an error that occurs when a query retrieves a result that differs from the supported result type.

errors.name: UnsupportedTypeError
errors.description: Represents an error that occurs when an unsupported parameter type is added to the query.

Generates a stream consisting of `sql:Error` elements.

records.description: Represents the properties belonging to an `sql:BatchExecuteError`.
Represents a check constraint.
Defines the database column name which matches the record field. The default value is the record field name.
Represents a column in a table.

Represents the properties, which are used to configure a DB connection pool.
Default values of the fields can be set through the configuration API.
Represents the properties belonging to an `sql:DatabaseError`.
Metadata of the query execution.
Represents a routine parameter.
Represents a referential constraint (foriegn key constraint).
Represents a routine.
Represents a table in the database.

constants.description: Constant indicating that the specific batch statement failed.

Constant indicating that the specific batch statement executed successfully
but that the count of affected rows is unavailable.

errors.description: Represents an error originating from application-level configurations.
Represents an error that occurs during the execution of batch queries.
Represents an error that occurs when a query retrieves a result that is corrupted and cannot be converted to the expected type.

Represents an error caused by an issue related to database accessibility, erroneous queries, constraint violations,
database resource clean-up, and other similar scenarios.
Represents an error that occurs during the processing of the parameters or returned results.
Defines the generic error type for the `sql` module.
Represents an error that occurs when a query retrieves a result that cannot be mapped to the expected record type.
Represents an error that occurs when a query retrieves does not retrieve any rows when at least one row is expected.
Represents an error that occurs when a query retrieves a result that differs from the supported result type.
Represents an error that occurs when an unsupported parameter type is added to the query.

annotations.description: The Annotation used to specify which database column matches the Typed record field.

objectTypes.description: The iterator for the stream returned in the `query` function to be used to override the default behavior of the `sql:ResultIterator`.
Represents the generic OUT Parameters in `sql:ParameterizedCallQuery`.

The object constructed through backtick surrounded strings. Dynamic parameters of `sql:Parameter` type can be indicated using `${<variable name>}`
such as `` `The sql:ParameterizedQuery is ${variable_name}` ``.
This validates the parameter types during the query execution.

The object constructed through backtick surrounded strings. Dynamic parameters of `sql:Value` type can be indicated using `${<variable name>}`
such as `` `The sql:ParameterizedQuery is ${variable_name}` ``.
This validates the parameter types during the query execution.
Generic type that can be passed to `sql:ParameterizedQuery` to represent parameters in the SQL query.

enums.description: Represents the mode of the parameter for a routine.
Represents the type of actions that would be taken on delete or on update for foreign key constraints.
Represents the type of the routine retrieved through the `getRoutineInfo` function.
Represents the type of the table/view retrieved through the `getTableInfo` function.
